    "body": "Thanks for writing this up @jimmygchen and shout out to [antithesis](https://antithesis.com/). \r\n\r\nI received the messages when the CL nodes came up and started connecting with other peers, but also a bit before forks.\r\n\r\nThere were two types of log messages. The one that you posted above where there are too many topic subscriptions in a request and another one below where the client tries to subscribe to a new topics, but already has too many subscriptions:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[   35812] [   761.715855] [service_lighthouse-besu-0--lighthouse-bn]       [I] [2023-08-04T10:17:52Z ERROR libp2p_gossipsub::behaviour] Subscription filter error: too many subscribed topics; ignoring RPC from peer 16Uiu2HAmMd144JvTzK5wVYC8HywSkZ2tvxRTnHwHKqw6Wc4shGPC\r\n```\r\n\r\nBoth limits `max_subscribed_topics` and `max_subscriptions_per_request` are being hit.",
